{
  "_README": [
    "Stage for every dexOnly Digimon whose sprite lives ONLY in `Idle Frame Only/`, which is not",
    "a stage folder — so nothing on disk says what stage these are, and `import_roster.py` emits",
    "them as `\"stage\": null`. `build_roster.py` resolves them through this table and REFUSES to",
    "write roster.json if any null-stage id is missing here, so a new idle-only sprite fails the",
    "build instead of shipping with a guessed stage.",
    "",
    "Hand-authored from the published level of each Digimon (Reference Book levels map to the",
    "folder names as: Fresh=Baby I, In-Training=Baby II, Rookie=Child, Champion=Adult,",
    "Ultimate=Perfect, Mega=Ultimate-Super Ultimate; Armor and Hybrid both=Armor-Hybrid).",
    "Entries carrying a `?` in this list are the ones whose published level I could not confirm;",
    "they are marked in `uncertain` below so a later pass can check them rather than trusting",
    "them silently. Being dexOnly, a wrong stage here only files a Dex entry under the wrong",
    "heading — it can never affect evolution, which never names a dexOnly Digimon."
  ],
